general_exclusion_criteria:
Severe cardiac comorbidity (heart failure or left ventricular ejection fraction ≤50%);
Severe pulmonary comorbidity (DLCO ≤65 % predicted, FEV₁ ≤65 % predicted, resting dyspnea, or oxygen dependence);
Corrected QT interval greater than 480 milliseconds;
Major surgery within 2 weeks preceding first dose;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses—including untreated infection, unstable cardiovascular conditions (symptomatic congestive heart failure NYHA III-IV, unstable angina, significant arrhythmia, recent MI or stroke), psychiatric disorders limiting compliance;
Requirement for continuous supplementary oxygen, mechanical ventilation, vasoactive drugs, or dialysis;
Active or unresolved hepatitis B/C infection, known HIV infection;
History of significant congenital or acquired bleeding diathesis unrelated to leukaemia;
Impairment of gastrointestinal absorption affecting oral drug uptake;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Use of prohibited concomitant medicines (strong CYP3A4/5 inducers or inhibitors, narrow‑therapeutic‑index CYP substrate drugs, proton pump inhibitors/H₂ blockers, grapefruit products).

