Progressive or stable disease on covalent BTK inhibitor;
Transformation of chronic lymphocytic leukemia to aggressive non‑Hodgkin lymphoma (Richter's transformation or pro‑lymphocytic leukemia);
History of cardiomyopathy;
Clinically significant cardiovascular disease;
Active bleeding or history of bleeding diathesis;
Pregnant women and nursing mothers;
Uncontrolled autoimmune hemolytic anemia or immune thrombocytopenia;
Hypersensitivity to venetoclax or to any of the excipients.

Fanconi anemia;
Shwachman‑Diamond syndrome;
Constitutional trisomy 21 or mosaic trisomy 21;
Telomere biology disorders;
Germline predisposition syndromes that raise toxicity risk with AML therapy;
Any concurrent malignancy;
Juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia;
Philadelphia chromosome‑positive acute myeloid leukemia;
Mixed phenotype acute leukemia;
Acute promyelocytic leukemia;
Acute myeloid leukemia evolving from antecedent myelodysplastic syndrome;
Therapy‑related myeloid neoplasms;
Persistent cardiac dysfunction before enrolment defined as left ventricular ejection fraction < 50 %;
Pregnancy in female participants;
Breastfeeding mothers planning to nurse during treatment;
Patients of reproductive potential unwilling or unable to use effective contraception throughout study participation;
Congenital long QT syndrome or congenital atrioventricular conduction block.

