History of or active severe bacterial, fungal, or viral infection requiring systemic therapy;
Major surgical procedure performed within four weeks preceding enrolment;
Ongoing anticancer chemotherapy or immunotherapy;
Ongoing radiation therapy;
Symptomatic spinal cord compression;
Presence of another active malignant disease requiring systemic therapy within the past two years;
Retinal vein occlusion history or existing significant risk factors for retinal vein occlusion;
Pregnancy or lactation in female participants;
Concurrent participation in another interventional clinical trial;
Previous use of experimental agents directed against the KRAS/BRAF/MEK/ERK signaling axis.

