Participants with disease transformed to aggressive lymphoma;
Patients with symptomatic or untreated hyperviscosity syndrome or IgM >4000 mg/dL who cannot receive/plasmaphere beforehand;
Concurrent participation in another investigational therapeutic trial;
Residual grade > 1 toxicities from prior anticancer therapy (except alopecia or peripheral neuropathy);
Unresolved serious infectious complications requiring inpatient care or IV antibiotics within 4 weeks;
Significant cardiovascular disease (NYHA class III–IV heart failure, left ventricular ejection fraction < 45 %, unstable angina, myocardial infarction <6 months, uncontrolled arrhythmias);
Active central nervous system pathology (seizure disorders, strokes, psychoses, dementias, CNS vasculitis, encephalitis);
Requirement for supplemental oxygen at rest to maintain SpO₂ > 92 %;
Systemic glucocorticoids ≥20 mg prednisolone equivalents daily or other chronic immunosuppression for non‑Waldénström indications within 28 days;
Known or presumed central nervous system involvement/leptomeningeal disease from Waldenström macroglobulinemia;
Pregnancy, lactation, or inability/unwillingness to comply with mandated contraception measures;
Current alcohol/substance misuse, significant psychiatric instability, or socially unsafe circumstances limiting protocol adherence;
History of hypersensitivity reaction to substances structurally/compositionally similar to epcoritamab;
Receipt of a live or live‑attenuated vaccination within 4 weeks preceding enrolment.

History of interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis requiring intervention (grade ≤1 pneumonitis acceptable except in triplet arms);
Type 1 or Type 2 diabetes requiring antihyperglycaemic medication or fasting plasma glucose ≥140 mg/dL or HbA1c ≥7.0%;
Hypersensitivity to PI3K pathway inhibitors, fulvestrant, palbociclib, ribociclib, or PF‑07220060;
Mean resting corrected QT interval >470 ms (>=450 ms for ribociclib arm) or personal/familial history of long QT/Torsade’s de Pointes;
Clinically significant, uncontrolled cardiovascular disease;
Active central nervous system metastases or primary CNS tumor with progressive neurologic symptoms;
Uncontrolled systemic infections including HIV, chronic hepatitis B or C;
Pregnancy, lactation, or unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Inadequate hepatic, renal, or bone marrow function meeting protocol laboratory thresholds;
ECOG performance status greater than 1.

