History of clinically significant cardiomyopathy or congestive heart failure;
Uncontrolled hypertension;
Clinically significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin > 1.5× ULN or AST/ALT > 3× ULN);
Renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance <40 mL/min);
Active infection requiring intravenous antibiotics;
Seropositivity for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (type 1 or 2), active Hepatitis B surface antigen positivity, or positive Hepatitis C antibodies;
Recent major surgery or trauma within 30 days;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Inadequate contraceptive measures for women of childbearing potential;
Concurrent anticancer therapy not permitted by protocol;
Any condition compromising ability to comply with study procedures or jeopardizing safety.

