History of interstitial lung disease that is symptomatic or interferes with detection of drug‑related pulmonary toxicity;
Uncontrolled asthma;
Current symptomatic congestive heart failure (NYHA Class III–IV) or left ventricular ejection fraction below institution’s lower limit of normal, or myocardial infarction, coronary or peripheral arterial bypass, stroke or transient ischemic attack within six months preceding study entry;
Uncontrolled hypertension (systolic > 160 mmHg or diastolic > 100 mmHg);
Significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin > 1.5× upper limit of normal or AST/ALT > 2.5× ULN absent liver metastases);
Severe renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance < 50 mL/min);
Active serious infections, including known HIV/AIDS, hepatitis B or C infection;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Known current alcohol or illicit drug dependence;
Prisoners or individuals involuntarily detained;
Any psychiatric, social, or medical condition deemed by the investigators to substantially increase risk or impede adherence to study protocols.

History of serious cardiovascular disease (symptomatic congestive heart failure NYHA Class II or greater, unstable angina, clinically significant arrhythmia);
Significant pulmonary disease (rest dyspnea or moderate/severe exertional dyspnea);
Active uncontrolled infection, including COVID‑19, HIV with detectable viremia, hepatitis B or C active infection;
Clinically significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin > 1.5× upper limit of normal, transaminases > 3× ULN);
Renal insufficiency (creatinine > 1.5 × ULN or CrCl < 50 mL/min);
Recent major surgery (within six weeks);
Palliative radiotherapy within two weeks;
Inability to ingest oral medication due to gastrointestinal obstruction, active inflammatory bowel disease, or extensive resections;
Grade 2 or higher peripheral neuropathy;
Known hypersensitivity to paclitaxel;
Prolonged corrected QT interval (> 480 ms) or use of drugs that markedly lengthen QT/QTc;
Risk factors for torsades de pointe (family long‑Qt syndrome, electrolyte abnormalities);
Use of strong cytochrome P450 3A4 enzyme inducers or inhibitors;
Other active malignant diseases except adequately treated basal/squamous non‑melanoma skin cancer, cured cervical intraepithelial neoplasia, or other solid tumours without recurrence for over two years;
Unstable mental health conditions limiting adherence to protocol.

