History of untreated or active CNS metastases (except stable treated lesions with steroid taper);
Symptomatic visceral crisis or >50 % hepatic involvement;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illness including serious cardiovascular disease, uncontrolled hypertension, recent myocardial infarction, congestive heart failure NYHA III-IV;
Active systemic infection, unresolved pneumonia, tuberculosis, hepatitis B/C with detectable viral load, HIV with detectable viral load;
Clinically significant pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease;
Recent major surgery (within 28 days) or wound healing problems;
Significant bleeding diathesis or coagulopathy;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or unwillingness to use effective contraceptive methods;
Concurrent malignant neoplasm requiring active therapy or within 3 years (excluding certain non‑melanoma skin cancers, superficial bladder cancer, cervical CIS);
Substance/alcohol dependence interfering with protocol compliance;
Any condition judged by the investigator to place the subject at undue risk or interfere with evaluation of the study.

