History of pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease, or evidence of pneumonitis/ILD on baseline imaging;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses including uncontrolled hypertension, active infection, symptomatic congestive heart failure, unstable angina, clinically significant cardiac arrhythmias, or severe psychiatric disorder impairing adherence;
QTcF greater than 470 milliseconds on screening electrocardiogram;
Past or current diagnosis of myelodysplastic syndrome or acute myeloid leukaemia, or signs suggesting evolving MDS/AML;
Concurrent use of strong or moderate cytochrome P450 enzymes inhibitors or inducers (especially CYP3A);
Inability to swallow oral medication or gastrointestinal conditions interfering with drug absorption (malabsorptive syndromes, extensive gastric/bowel resection);
Recent major surgical procedures within 28 days before starting protocol therapy;
Active or untreated tuberculosis infection;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding; women of childbearing potential and sexually active men must use effective contraception during study and for four months afterward.

