Isolated central nervous system disease of mature B‑cell NHL without systemic involvement and primary CNS lymphoma;
Ongoing adverse events from prior anticancer therapy not resolved to Grade ≤ 1 (except alopecia, Grade 2 peripheral neuropathy);
Grade ≥ 3 adverse events (exception: endocrine toxicity manageable with hormone replacement);
Active untreated infections at day 1 of cycle 1;
History of solid organ transplantation;
Known or suspected haemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis or chronic active EBV infection;
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic therapy;
Severe hypersensitivity or anaphylaxis to monoclonal antibodies or murine-derived agents;
Confirmed progressive multifocal leucoencephalopathy;
Uncontrolled non‑malignant neurological disorders (stroke, epilepsy, CNS vasculitis, neurodegeneration);
Significant unmanaged concurrent illnesses compromising protocol adherence;
Major surgical procedure or serious trauma within 28 days preceding pre‑treatment infusion;
Administration of live attenuated vaccination within 4 weeks before starting study treatment or anytime during treatment phase, and within 12 months post‑study;
Any other medical, psychiatric, or social circumstance judged unsuitable for participation.

